article.headline: Duquesne 78, Youngstown State 54
article.story: PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Bryant McAllister scored 16 points and Kieron Achara added another 14 as Duquesne defeated Youngstown St. 78-54 Friday afternoon. The Dukes (3-10) came in having lost nine of 10 but never trailed during the game. Duquesne went on two separate 7-0 runs in the first half and scored the first 12 points after halftime to extend its lead to 42-18. The Dukes led by as many as 27 in the second half. Freshman DeVario Hudson scored 12 points. Quin Humphrey scored 16 points and had 10 rebounds and freshman Colin LaForme scored 10 points for Youngstown (3-8). Led by Achara's five blocks, Duquesne had 10 blocked shots in the game, the most since 1990. The Penguins, who have now lost eight of their last nine, shot only 29 percent from the field, the lowest shooting output for a Duquesne opponent in three years.
